25:21.311 --> 25:25.696
Jesus is explicitly denying that as his ethic.

25:27.398 --> 25:28.038
Verse 34.

25:30.241 --> 25:35.867
If you lend to those from whom you expect to receive, what credit is that to you?

25:38.009 --> 25:42.194
Even sinners lend to sinners to get back the same amount

25:44.354 --> 25:48.879
Rather, Jesus says in verse 35, love.

25:49.179 --> 25:50.360
Here's love explicitly.

25:50.380 --> 25:51.362
Here's love.

25:51.382 --> 26:05.497
Love your enemies and do good and lend expecting nothing in return from them and your reward will be great.

26:07.299 --> 26:07.979
See the move there?

26:08.280 --> 26:09.101
Nothing from them.

26:09.121 --> 26:10.682
You give here.

26:10.702 --> 26:11.583
You don't get here.

26:11.603 --> 26:12.164
You give here.

26:12.404 --> 26:14.066
You get here from your father.

26:16.578 --> 26:29.132
The credit here or the benefit to which Jesus makes explicit appeal is not what others do for you in return, but what your heavenly father will be and do for you.

26:30.354 --> 26:38.062
You give to others seeking nothing in return from them because you are looking to the reward you get from your father.

26:39.644 --> 26:40.726
So get this straight.

26:43.008 --> 26:44.690
We are seeking return.

26:46.338 --> 26:50.064
We're looking for reward, but not from man.

26:50.104 --> 26:53.289
That's too small.

26:54.951 --> 26:56.434
It doesn't last very long.

26:57.736 --> 27:01.341
We're looking for reward returned from God.

27:02.924 --> 27:06.730
When he gives, he doesn't hold back like man does.

27:07.832 --> 27:09.875
He doesn't cut corners in his giving.

27:10.175 --> 27:12.920
He doesn't ration limited resources.

27:13.180 --> 27:14.482
He lavishes

27:14.594 --> 27:17.397
infinite resources on his people.

27:20.300 --> 27:26.006
This comes back to the good measure, press down, shaking together, running over.

27:26.066 --> 27:31.512
Maybe in the modern world, we might compare that to an ice cream cone.

27:35.115 --> 27:41.682
We have an ice cream shop in the Twin Cities called Nelson's, probably Swedish ancestry.

27:44.290 --> 27:48.635
And Nelson's as known as being over the top generous.

27:49.476 --> 28:02.993
So if you're hungry for ice cream, you're looking at all the flavors, you pick your flavor, you pick your cone, and the worker back there is probably a teenager, the worker back there, they scoop a little bit, and they put it on top, and you look at like, what?

28:03.213 --> 28:04.134
They just put it on top.

28:04.154 --> 28:05.856
I know the whole cone is empty.

28:07.117 --> 28:09.240
But at Nelson's, they're known for this.

28:10.401 --> 28:12.924
At Nelson's, they're gonna give you good measure.

28:13.245 --> 28:14.226
Not gonna get a bunch.

28:14.530 --> 28:15.872
They're going to press it down.

28:15.932 --> 28:16.694
It's ice cream.

28:16.734 --> 28:17.615
You don't shake it together.

28:17.635 --> 28:18.196
They press it down.

28:18.217 --> 28:19.779
They press it all the way into the cone.

28:20.821 --> 28:23.726
And then running over is their specialty.

28:24.027 --> 28:25.570
I mean, it's almost a joke.

28:25.670 --> 28:28.895
It is laughable for people who come to Nelson's for the first time.

28:29.537 --> 28:30.518
You have to tell him ahead of time.

28:30.538 --> 28:32.482
Folks who have been there before, you're used to it.

28:33.123 --> 28:33.744
It's laughable.

28:34.004 --> 28:35.126
They pile it on.

28:35.347 --> 28:35.968
They pile it on.

28:36.268 --> 28:37.170
So tall.

28:37.314 --> 28:38.275
It's about to fall over.

28:38.475 --> 28:40.657
You can order a child size ice cream.

28:40.697 --> 28:42.279
Now this wouldn't be allowed in Sweden, right?

28:42.319 --> 28:45.282
The government would shut Nelson's down.

28:47.904 --> 28:48.725
This is America.

28:50.467 --> 28:52.709
Order a child size and get a gallon of ice cream.

28:54.491 --> 28:56.192
They pile it on top.

28:56.292 --> 29:00.136
So when I go to Nelson's, I don't eat a child size by myself.

29:00.236 --> 29:02.058
I share it with one of my children.

29:02.799 --> 29:06.322
My family of six, we can order three child size ice creams.

29:07.074 --> 29:08.837
and all eat to our hearts content.

29:10.579 --> 29:14.425
And it is such a picture of the lavishness of our God.

29:15.687 --> 29:17.089
It's not leaving the cone empty.

29:17.109 --> 29:18.331
He's piling it on top.

29:18.351 --> 29:19.533
He's punching it down.

29:19.553 --> 29:21.556
It's so big it's about to fall over.

29:21.576 --> 29:23.479
You got to grab it with a plate or a cup.

29:25.101 --> 29:26.844
So number one, look six.

29:27.224 --> 29:28.847
God will outgive you.

29:28.967 --> 29:30.189
He will outlove you.

29:30.229 --> 29:33.834
I promise you will not outlove the Almighty God.

29:33.894 --> 29:36.338
And knowing that you are freed to give.

29:36.898 --> 29:41.704
There will be no deficit for those who love well.

29:42.024 --> 29:48.331
Number two, God gives treasure that will not fail.

29:50.514 --> 29:54.418
Now we're jumping forward to Luke 12, verses 32 to 34.

29:55.019 --> 29:59.204
God gives treasure that will not fail.

30:04.009 --> 30:04.850
Verse 32.

30:06.146 --> 30:07.367
Fear not, little flock.

30:10.211 --> 30:15.697
For it is your father's good pleasure to give you the kingdom.

30:17.460 --> 30:19.222
Oh, I just love that little flock.

30:20.603 --> 30:24.308
Modest, marginal, small, weak, little flock.

30:24.608 --> 30:27.452
He's going to give you the kingdom.

30:30.976 --> 30:31.657
Running over.

30:33.759 --> 30:36.082
Sell your possessions and give.

30:36.546 --> 30:37.147
to the needy.

30:38.228 --> 30:41.011
Provide yourselves with money bags that do not grow old.

30:41.371 --> 30:43.874
With a treasure in the heavens, it does not fail.

30:43.934 --> 30:54.426
Where no thief approaches and no moth destroys, for where your treasure is, there your heart will be also.

30:56.308 --> 31:04.978
So this is the same spirit and holy joy seeking as we see in Jesus' other ethic, in his line of reasoning.

31:05.890 --> 31:22.649
As you empty your earthly, aging, stealable wallets by giving to others who are in need, you provide yourselves with heavenly money bags that do not grow old, treasure that cannot be stolen by thieves or destroyed by moths.

31:24.371 --> 31:26.934
So again, we're finding this two directions of giving.

31:27.534 --> 31:28.155
We've already seen it.

31:29.416 --> 31:32.380
Number one, Jesus people give to others in need.

31:32.400 --> 31:34.482
And number two,

31:35.490 --> 31:38.214
Jesus' father gives to his people.

31:39.116 --> 31:42.120
Coming down from heaven, might give to others.

31:42.441 --> 31:49.151
You give from your limited possessions to the needy and you get from your father's unlimited bounty.

31:49.833 --> 31:53.899
And remembering that motivates the giving.

31:55.381 --> 31:56.583
Jesus doesn't want us to forget that.

31:57.284 --> 31:58.546
He's motivating us by that.

31:59.127 --> 32:03.474
Remembering your father, his lavishness, his giving motivates us.

32:05.442 --> 32:12.633
knowing that your father has it all and that what he has cannot be stolen or destroyed.

32:12.673 --> 32:16.459
And that he happily gives to his children and doesn't hold back.

32:16.700 --> 32:21.187
You are freed from hoarding and holding tightly to your earthly possessions.

32:22.348 --> 32:23.550
That includes time and energy.

32:25.413 --> 32:27.697
And this appeal is plainly joy-seeking.

32:27.997 --> 32:30.641
Give to the needy, recalling your father has no needs.

32:31.763 --> 32:33.586
Not only does he care for his little flock,

32:34.402 --> 32:36.224
and thus free you to care for others.

32:37.125 --> 32:43.931
But in your very giving to others, you accrue more blessing from your father.

32:45.412 --> 32:53.500
You are more blessed, Jesus says, to give to others and so to receive from your father in heaven.

32:55.742 --> 32:57.224
More free to love.

32:57.604 --> 32:59.386
This giving is an act of love.

33:00.266 --> 33:04.050
Believing that your father gives treasure that doesn't fail

33:04.578 --> 33:10.004
And seeking that treasure frees you in love to give to those in need.

33:10.304 --> 33:15.089
Number two, number three, God will make you happy.

33:17.191 --> 33:20.034
It's so simple, but it's so profound.

33:22.717 --> 33:23.638
This is Luke 14.

33:26.141 --> 33:27.702
God will make you happy.

33:28.683 --> 33:31.346
Luke 14 verses 13 to 14.

33:35.426 --> 33:48.388
When you give a feast, invite the poor, the crippled, the lame, the blind, and you will be blessed because they cannot repay you.

33:49.289 --> 33:50.752
Are you starting to pick up on the logic here?

33:51.773 --> 33:56.281
You're going to be blessed because they can't repay you.

33:57.242 --> 33:58.104
Uh oh, what does that leave?

33:58.164 --> 34:01.810
That leaves space for your father.

34:03.106 --> 34:08.031
For you will be repaid at the resurrection of the just.

34:08.812 --> 34:14.237
So this one, Luke 14 here, comes the closest to Acts 2035 of all of them.

34:14.257 --> 34:20.423
They're all nearby, but this is probably the closest because it mentions being blessed, happy.

34:20.863 --> 34:22.665
It mentions the call to give.

34:23.466 --> 34:26.869
It mentions the promise of repayment or reward.

34:27.930 --> 34:30.072
And this is not the blessed of being praised.

34:30.352 --> 34:32.114
This is the blessed of being happy.

34:33.826 --> 34:39.152
When you give to others and they cannot repay you, God will make you happy.

34:39.192 --> 34:51.786
He will repay you in the end and knowing that makes us not only happy in the end, but through faith streams to us in the present.

34:51.806 --> 35:02.098
This is really a profound insight in this text into Jesus' ethic when he mentions others who cannot repay you.

35:03.522 --> 35:10.248
That's setting up the scenario that provides clarity about the ethic.

35:10.268 --> 35:16.554
The natural human, less happy way is to give to others who will give back to you.

35:18.476 --> 35:19.737
They'll repay you, tip for tap.

35:20.118 --> 35:22.340
That's just normal human interaction.

35:23.721 --> 35:33.330
You have your reward from that human and you leave there untapped infinite joy resources

35:33.634 --> 35:35.036
from heaven and eternity.

35:36.818 --> 35:43.406
But the supernatural, divine, more blessed way is to give to others who cannot repay you.

35:45.308 --> 35:49.934
Because then you know that your heart has been truly seeking real joy.

35:49.954 --> 35:58.684
Your heart has looked to the majestic rewards of heaven rather than the measly reimbursements of earth.

36:00.466 --> 36:03.410
And your heavenly Father has never missed a single

36:03.650 --> 36:07.975
He will repay you in His perfect justice.

36:08.336 --> 36:11.419
He will reward you with everything you deserve.

36:12.140 --> 36:17.106
And in addition to that, in His amazing grace, He will lavish you with far more than you deserve.

36:18.748 --> 36:25.316
You will be happier by far to be rewarded by Him than to be repaid by fellow humans.

36:26.578 --> 36:33.586
And through that freeing, joy-seeking intention, you will be enabled in that moment.

36:34.082 --> 36:36.666
to love, rather than be selfish.

36:38.168 --> 36:50.726
You love knowing that you're all seeing, all knowing, all just, all gracious Heavenly Father will not let any act in the name of His Son go without reward.

36:52.909 --> 36:55.893
The glory of His Son is at stake.

36:55.913 --> 36:57.636
However hidden it may be in this age.

36:57.936 --> 36:59.478
One day the books are going to be open.

37:00.961 --> 37:02.002
The world will know.

37:02.402 --> 37:13.215
Jesus will be honored and our Heavenly Father will shower His children with everything good they are owed and far, far more lavishly than what they deserve.

37:15.678 --> 37:24.189
Jesus said that even one who gives a cup of cold water in His name will by no means lose His reward.

37:26.211 --> 37:31.538
How much more one who gives a feast to the needy and lives the life of love.

37:32.322 --> 37:34.004
Number four then, last one.

37:36.066 --> 37:37.088
This is in Luke 16.

37:39.751 --> 37:42.374
God will receive you into his house.

37:44.716 --> 37:51.604
Luke 16 verse nine, this is the most peculiar of the four passages.

37:52.085 --> 37:54.988
God will receive you into his house.

37:56.590 --> 37:59.954
Jesus tells this parable of the unrighteous manager

38:00.290 --> 38:07.157
who shrewdly uses his temporary access to wealth to secure favor for himself once the stewardship is taken away.

38:09.579 --> 38:12.662
And Jesus acknowledges that what this steward does is unrighteous.

38:13.403 --> 38:19.188
He's not telling his disciples to go do that, but he's teaching an important lesson in this parable, in this scenario.

38:19.949 --> 38:24.753
So he risks drawing on this joy-seeking lesson for his disciples.

38:24.773 --> 38:26.895
This is verse nine of chapter 16.

38:28.177 --> 38:29.618
Make friends for yourself

38:29.794 --> 38:40.905
by means of unrighteous wealth, which you have in this age, so that when it fails, and it will, they may receive you into the eternal dwellings.

38:44.048 --> 38:50.214
All right, we've seen this logic before, even if it hasn't been quite as provocative as this parable.

38:52.156 --> 38:57.842
Our possessions on earth and our time on earth and our energy in this life are so

38:57.954 --> 39:01.017
So soon they will fail us.

39:02.999 --> 39:05.141
Why hold on to them and be ruined?

39:07.203 --> 39:16.031
When you could use what you have right now, the stewardship you have now to make friends for yourself with God Almighty.

39:16.072 --> 39:20.356
That's who the friends are in the parable.

39:20.376 --> 39:21.857
He says, make friends.

39:22.838 --> 39:24.219
The plural is from the parable.

39:24.820 --> 39:26.962
What's intended is God Himself.

39:27.202 --> 39:33.031
You've got one friend in mind who will receive you into his eternal dwelling.

39:33.912 --> 39:36.917
This is an appeal to joy, plain and simple.

39:38.299 --> 39:43.086
Holding on now to earthly possessions will not make you deeply and enduringly happy.

39:45.269 --> 39:54.964
If you really want to be happy, if you want real joy, loosen your grip.

39:54.984 --> 39:56.146
Give generously.

39:57.378 --> 40:05.613
not that you might receive in return from fellow humans, but that you might receive now and for forever from your father in heaven.

40:05.673 --> 40:15.630
And one day as a guest and even more than that, as a child, you will be taken into the home that is heaven.

40:18.595 --> 40:22.322
So it is more blessed to give

40:22.594 --> 40:27.179
than to receive, I think, is a marvelous summary of Jesus' ethic.

40:27.219 --> 40:28.681
We could go on to other examples.

40:28.981 --> 40:34.407
There's four examples of Jesus teaching it's more blessed to give than to receive.

40:34.467 --> 40:45.879
So how might it become tangible than for us in moments of decision, moments that call for an act of love, for generosity with our time, our finances, our energy, our attention?

40:50.004 --> 40:51.986
When faced with the opportunity to give,

40:53.474 --> 41:01.262
in the call to love, Jesus would say, consider your holy joy.

41:01.302 --> 41:06.327
He didn't tell us all these things to forget about real joy.

41:08.409 --> 41:13.214
He says, remember, remember your holy joy.

41:13.274 --> 41:16.537
That's what Jesus would have us do.

41:16.557 --> 41:17.498
That's what Paul did.

41:17.538 --> 41:21.042
That's why he says, remember, remember your real joy.

41:21.218 --> 41:22.699
It will not ruin you.

41:23.020 --> 41:28.105
It will release you to love if you remember real joy.

41:29.246 --> 41:31.688
So very practically you come to a moment of decision.

41:33.330 --> 41:34.070
You hear of a need.

41:35.992 --> 41:37.474
Christian love is calling.

41:38.935 --> 41:43.259
You can think of all sorts of selfish reasons not to do it.

41:44.500 --> 41:47.743
And you can think of pretty human natural reasons.

41:47.764 --> 41:50.386
You might say, yes, what you might receive in return.

41:50.754 --> 41:51.695
on the horizontal level.

41:52.576 --> 41:59.225
And at that moment, Jesus and Paul would have us turn our minds to the promises of God.

42:00.347 --> 42:01.308
This is very practical.

42:01.488 --> 42:03.711
In that moment, where do you go with your mind?

42:03.751 --> 42:06.715
Turn to the promises of God.

42:08.077 --> 42:13.565
You might remind yourself, he will out give your giving guarantee.

42:14.646 --> 42:15.768
He'll out love your loving.

42:16.889 --> 42:20.594
Or you might remind yourself, he gives treasure that will not fail.

42:22.242 --> 42:30.116
or he will make you happy forever in measure right now and fully for forever.

42:30.156 --> 42:41.575
And in the end, he will even receive you into the endless divine generosity of his own house.

42:42.978 --> 42:44.080
Why would I not love?

42:45.041 --> 42:45.843
Why would I not give?

42:46.904 --> 42:47.826
I want real joy.

42:50.242 --> 42:52.304
unblushing promises of reward.

42:54.086 --> 43:01.653
Grab one of them, rehearse it, and then act in faith, believing the promise for your real joy.

43:01.673 --> 43:17.087
Or if you need a summary, if all else fails you, a text doesn't come to mind, you can grab Acts 20, 35, which is an inspired summary of the teaching of Jesus.

43:18.649 --> 43:20.050
He does more blessed

43:20.290 --> 43:24.755
you will be happier to give to others than receive from them.

43:26.538 --> 43:28.840
Now, back to the question at the beginning here as we close.

43:29.882 --> 43:31.323
First, the question about God.

43:33.406 --> 43:36.369
Is it loving for God to pursue His glory?

43:37.971 --> 43:39.613
Answer, yes.

43:40.895 --> 43:50.066
In fact, He would be unloving to not pursue and display and put before our eyes His own glory.

43:51.042 --> 43:54.986
He is the one who is supremely valuable and satisfying.

43:55.907 --> 44:04.036
If he were to forsake himself as God, he would not love us, but ruin us, condemn us to misery.

44:06.079 --> 44:13.067
If he points us to anything other than himself for real joy, he misleads or deceives or destroys us.

44:15.409 --> 44:17.752
That'd be hatred, not love.

44:19.033 --> 44:19.794
For God,

44:20.802 --> 44:29.416
Love is putting his glory and his son's glory on display for us that we might find real joy in him.

44:30.799 --> 44:31.560
What about for us?

44:33.944 --> 44:37.009
Is it loving for us to pursue joy in God?

44:39.152 --> 44:47.346
Will the loved ones in our lives truly feel loved and be loved if we seek our real joy in God and his glory?

44:50.786 --> 44:53.851
I can't promise you that they will feel loved.

44:57.376 --> 45:02.304
You're not responsible for their heart, for what they feel.

45:04.607 --> 45:16.325
You are responsible for acting according to who God is and His Word, and what is in fact loving in your soul, in seeking real joy, not simply what feels loving for them.

45:16.365 --> 45:19.570
Wherever they're at in their headspace related to God,

45:21.154 --> 45:26.983
But unless we seek our real joy in God, we cannot love others as we ought.

45:28.786 --> 45:35.115
Without joy in God, we will not have the overflow of joy to move with love towards others' needs.

45:36.838 --> 45:43.909
God's promises of reward free us from selfishness to pursue better joys through loving others.

45:45.952 --> 45:47.314
And without joy in God,

45:47.618 --> 45:52.925
we will not point our loved ones to the only source of real joy.

45:54.247 --> 46:02.338
The reason they may not feel loved is because they may not acknowledge God as the only source of real joy.

46:04.100 --> 46:17.138
So in the call of love, in the call to do something hard, or sometimes the harder thing to say something hard, to open your mouth to that neighbor

46:17.282 --> 46:21.627
about the gospel or that loved one, maybe even a stranger.

46:21.668 --> 46:35.545
Remember joy, rehearse a promise of reward, believe the promise and in faith take a risk to love.

46:36.406 --> 46:43.996
And however it goes, your father will reward you and you will not regret his reward.

46:45.317 --> 46:45.778
Let's pray.

46:47.234 --> 47:05.217
So Father in Heaven, for these dear brothers and sisters now, I come to the end of this conference, and we are commissioned back to our callings, various cities, even various countries, our households, our churches.

47:07.079 --> 47:15.890
Oh Father, would you send us, with the spirit of Jesus' teaching, send us with a holy, joy-seeking ethic

47:16.162 --> 47:34.391
that brings about concrete, real love in our lives, that we'd be able to say the thing that feels hard, that feels awkward, but needs to be said from love, that we'd not be selfish and gathering our own time and stuff and energy and attention but willing to give, take the risk to bless others and do something good.

47:35.893 --> 47:43.986
Father, I pray that this focus this weekend on real joy would have real implications

47:44.482 --> 47:56.514
a real outflow, real applications, real effects in our lives, that you change us, change the way we think, fill our hearts in such a way that we want to act.

47:56.554 --> 47:58.977
We don't want to go back to all the same old patterns.

47:59.978 --> 48:01.159
We want to be changed.

48:01.620 --> 48:05.524
We want to be ready to act for love, ready to speak for love.

48:09.488 --> 48:11.570
And you've given us your Holy Spirit.

48:11.874 --> 48:22.089
We are not on our own in the call for love, but dwelt by you in your spirit through your son.

48:22.149 --> 48:27.677
And to Father, would you send us now for joy and in love to your glory?

48:28.458 --> 48:29.360
In Jesus' name we pray.

48:30.581 --> 48:30.962
Amen.

